### Problem Description

When all test documents are in the same segment, using script fields to get the second value of an array in a document,
the previous doc has a field named domain_id with value [1, 8], the next doc has the field which has the value [1]
when use
```
"script_fields": {
	"val": {
		"script": {
			"source": "doc.domain_id.values[1]",
			"lang": "painless"
		}
	}
}
```
to get domain_id's second value, the result is 8,8, but 8,0 is right.

### Steps to Reproduce

1、create an index as follows
```
PUT localhost:9200/test
{
	"settings": {
		"refresh_interval": "120s",#ensure all documents is written to the same segment "number_of_shards": 1,
		"number_of_replicas": 0
	},
	"mappings": {
		"arrays": {
			"dynamic": false,
			"properties": {
				"domain_id": {
					"type": "integer"
				}
			}
		}
	}
}

```
2、write some data
```
PUT localhost:9200/_bulk
{ "index" : { "_index" : "test", "_type": "arrays", "_id": 1}}
{"domain_id":[1]}
{ "index" : { "_index" : "test", "_type": "arrays", "_id": 2}}
{"domain_id":[1]}
